## REPO RULES
- Lambdas: src/<component>/handler.py + tests/test_<component>.py
- ASL state machines: infra/*.asl.json
- Glue + Athena: scripts/provision_m6_glue.sh + sql/m6-*.sql
- IaC: infra/template.yaml (AWS SAM)
- Audit folders (committed): prompts/ reviews/ design/ sql/
- Region locked: ap-south-1; CLI examples hardcode, code uses env var (AWS_REGION)
- Branches: module-N-<learner>; MRs only — no direct commits to main

## CONSTRAINTS
- Bedrock: invoke via APAC inference PROFILE (not raw model ID):
    apac.anthropic.claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022-v2:0
- Bedrock budget: max 50 invocations + 20,000 tokens per learner per session.
- Bedrock FORBIDDEN in this sandbox: Studio, Knowledge Bases, Agents, AgentCore.
- Lambda: max 10 functions per learner across programme; max 2048 MB memory;
  runtime python3.12; default timeout 60s (modules may override per-lab —
  e.g. ETL Lambda on D6 uses 180s, SageMaker wrapper on D9 uses 30s).
- SageMaker: max 1 endpoint; provisioned: allowed CPU instance families only;
  D9 uses Serverless (MemorySizeInMB + MaxConcurrency); NO GPU instances.
- Glue: max 3 jobs (type=glueetl); max 4 DPU per job; max 6 DPU-hours cumulative
  across whole programme; sessions disabled. Crawlers DO NOT count against the
  ≤3 jobs cap.
- DynamoDB: PAY_PER_REQUEST billing for idempotency tables; no GSIs required.
- Athena: workgroup `accelya_<learner>` enforces BytesScannedCutoffPerQuery
  (100 MB default; Lab 3 drops to 10 MB temporarily). `EnforceWorkGroupConfiguration=true`.
- FIS (Fault Injection): max 20 minutes action time per lab.
- GitHub: public starter repo; MRs only; manual cleanup-sandbox after each module.
- AWS Budgets: NOT supported in sandbox — use CW metric-math alarms.
- Cost Explorer API: NOT enabled in sandbox — use CW metric proxies.
- Step Functions: 256 KiB execution state limit. NEVER pass `rows[]` through state;
  chunks live in S3 staging, only chunk_keys travel through ASL.

