## CATALOG CONTEXT
# Use this block when Cascade scaffolds reads/writes against Glue Catalog
# or generates Athena SQL. Applies to: etl_json_to_parquet, all SQL files,
# any future Day-7+ enricher that reads from curated/.

- Two-table model (Lab 1 provisions both):
    accelya_curated_<learner>.settlement
        (Parquet — primary read target; Snappy compression)
    accelya_validated_<learner>.validated_settlement_json
        (JSON SerDe — kept for cost-comparison only; do NOT add new readers)

- Format:
    Parquet (Snappy)  — curated/ zone (write target for ETL Lambda)
    JSON SerDe         — validated/ zone (read-only after Day 5 ASL pipeline)

- Partition keys (BOTH tables, identical layout):
    source_system  (STRING)  — values: BSP | ARC | ATPCO | GDS
    ingest_date    (STRING — Crawler default; lab queries treat as STRING)
    Hive-style paths in S3:
        validated/<learner>/validated_settlement_json/
            source_system=BSP/ingest_date=2026-05-09/<file>.jsonl
        curated/settlement/
            ingest_date=2026-05-09/source_system=BSP/part-00000.parquet

- Schema version: v3 (current)
    v1 (2026-04): {settlement_id, airline_code, fare_amount}
    v2 (2026-05): + currency, commission_pct
    v3 (2026-W19): + ticket_number, bsp_cycle
- Known evolution:
    'amount' inbound from some sources → mapped to fare_amount by ETL
    agency_iata may be NULL for v1 rows

- Read pattern (preferred):
    SQL over the catalog table — NEVER read raw Parquet files directly
    Partition pruning on `ingest_date + source_system` is MANDATORY
    SELECT only the columns needed — NEVER `SELECT *` on Parquet
    Always include WHERE on at least one partition column

- Write pattern (curated zone):
    Parquet (Snappy), partitioned by `ingest_date + source_system`
    One file per partition per ETL run (atomic publish)
    Use PyArrow + AWSSDKPandas layer in Lambda (≤50K rows/file)
    Use Glue Job (2 DPU, 15 min) for larger files
    NEVER write JSON to curated/

- Forbidden patterns (HITL Schema Discipline scores 0):
    SELECT * on a Parquet table
    Query without a partition filter
    JSON output to curated/<table>/
    Crawler over raw/ or another learner's prefix
    Glue Job > 4 DPU per job, or cumulative > 6 DPU-h

- ETL Lambda contract:
    function name: accelya-etl-json-to-parquet-<learner>
    runtime: python3.12 (x86_64)
    memory: 1024 MB; timeout: 180 s
    layer: AWSSDKPandas-Python312 (trainer-provided; ARN via $PANDAS_LAYER_ARN env var)
    event in: { file_key, source_system, ingest_date, chunk_id }
    return:   { status, rows_in, rows_out, parquet_key, file_sha256_in, file_sha256_out }
    schema:   fixed via pa.schema(...) — new columns silently dropped until schema updated

## EXAMPLES
- Cancellation envelope:
    { event_id, event_type: 'cancellation', airline_code: 'AI', pnr: '6X7Y8Z',
      booking_date: '2026-05-09', cancel_reason_code: 'WX', fare_amount: 2845.0 }
- Settlement record:
    { settlement_id: 'BSP-2026-W19-AI234-001', bsp_cycle: '2026-W19',
      airline_code: 'AI', pnr: '6X7Y8Z', fare_class: 'Y', od_pair: 'BOM-LHR',
      ticket_number: '098-1234567890', issue_date: '2026-05-08T11:42:00+05:30',
      fare_amount: 2845.00, currency: 'INR', commission_pct: 0.07,
      refund_status: null, agency_iata: '14305820', source_system: 'BSP' }
- Quarantine sidecar JSON:
    { reason: '<schema_drift|partial|malformed|business_rule_failed>',
      source_file: '<s3 key>', line_no: <int>,
      correlation_id: '<lambda request id>',
      validator_version: '<semver>',
      original_record: { ... } }
- Idempotency table: idempotency_keys_<learner> — single table, 4 guards:
    PK 'row#<file_key>:<line_no>'              (TTL 30d)
    PK 'file#<file_sha256>'                    (TTL 90d)
    PK 'canonical#<canonical_manifest_hash>'   (TTL 90d)
    PK 'business#<settlement_id>'              (TTL 30d)
- ASL state names (validator-pipeline.asl.json):
    Chunk -> HasRows -> Validate (Map) -> Land
                      -> NoRows
    Catch: QuarantineSchemaDrift, QuarantinePartial, QuarantineMalformed, NotifyOps
- ASL state names (dlq-replayer.asl.json):
    DrainDLQ -> Classify -> NotifyOps (sns:publish) | Done
- Athena reconciliation queries (sql/m6-reconciliation-5.sql):
    Q1 settlement-by-airline, Q2 missing-tickets, Q3 refund-rate-by-OD,
    Q4 top-OD-pairs-by-fare, Q5 fare-anomalies-vs-7d-median
- IAM ListBucket: Condition.s3:prefix pattern, NOT Resource suffix
- Reference artefacts in this project:
