## REVIEW
- Every Cascade-generated artefact passes 6-dim HITL checklist before merge:
    Correctness · Security · Observability · Scalability · Cost · Schema Discipline
- HITL_REVIEW-<artefact>.md filled per output + committed;
  PASS at >=14/18 AND every dim >=2/3
- Schema Discipline dim (NEW in v3) checks:
    - Partition keys match query patterns
    - Schema evolution path documented (additive / breaking / hard-breaking)
    - Columnar projection enforced (no SELECT *)
    - Parquet+Snappy on writes; no JSON in curated/
    - Crawler scoped to learner prefix; never cohort-shared
- ASL JSON is a reviewable artefact in v2+. The 5-dim rubric applies plus
  Schema Discipline if the ASL touches catalog tables.
- Retry MUST use named errors. NEVER `States.ALL`.
- IAM: NEVER wildcards in Action or Resource; named verbs + ARN-scoped resources.
- IAM: ListBucket scoped via Condition.s3:prefix.
- Logging: structured JSON with corr_id; NEVER print().
- Errors: classified into PipelineError ladder. Day 6 adds SchemaInferenceError
  (raised when Crawler discovers conflicting types across files).
- Idempotency: 4 guards in one DynamoDB table with prefixed PKs.
- Region: every CLI example uses --region ap-south-1; every code path reads from env var.
- Synthetic data only.
- batchItemFailures: ONLY for transient infra failures.
- Athena: ALL queries via the `accelya_<learner>` workgroup; bytes cap enforced.
